Legs and antennae uniformly reddish. Elytra slightly shorter and more slender, 0.75-0.80 times as long as pronotum (
Fig. 32
).

: sternite VII with posterior margin truncate, on either side of middle with approximately 8 long submarginal setae (
Fig. 33
); sternite VIII with rather sparse pubescence and with small posterior excision, its depth approximately 1/10 the length of sternite, otherwise unmodified (
Fig. 34
); aedeagus similar to that of 

S. macrops

, but apex of ventral process of different shape (
Figs 35-36
); internal structures similar to those of 

S. macrops

(
Fig. 37
).

